Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

== Butter Bean Stew ==

Start with the stew by peeling and cutting the @onion{1/2}(peeled and finely sliced into half moons). Peel and finely chop the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and chopped), chop the @vine tomatoes{2}(chopped into eighths) and heat a #medium-sized saucepan{} with a splash of @olive oil{a splash}. Once warm, add your onions and garlic. Fry for ~{5%mins} until they become soft, transparent and begin to colour.

Add the tomatoes to the #saucepan{} and cook for a further ~{2%mins}. Drain the @butter beans{1%tin} and add them to the pan, followed by the @chicken stock pot{1/2}, @tomato purée{1/2}, @bay leaf{1} and the @water{75%ml}. Place a lid on the saucepan and leave to simmer for ~{30%mins}, stirring occasionally to ensure it isn't catching on the bottom or becoming too dry.

> If it does start to become dry, just add a splash of water.

== New Potatoes ==

Chop any larger @new potatoes{1}(chopped) in half. Boil a #pot{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and add the new potatoes. Cook for ~{15%mins}.

Meanwhile, remove the core and slice the @red pepper{1}(core removed and sliced into thick strips about 2cm wide). Place these on a #baking tray{}.

== Paprika Pork ==

Season the @pork fillet{1} with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and rub the @smoked paprika{to taste} all over the meat. Place this on top of your bed of peppers and generously drizzle with @olive oil{generous drizzle}, before putting it on the top shelf of your oven for ~{15-20%mins} or until cooked through and no longer pink in the middle.

== Crushed New Potatoes ==

Your new potatoes should be thoroughly cooked now.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Drain them and lightly crush them with a #fork{} (don't mash them). Heat a medium-sized #frying pan{} with a splash of @olive oil{a splash}. Add your lightly crushed new potatoes to the frying pan. Fry for ~{4%mins}, until your potatoes start to crisp.

== Assembly ==

Your butter bean stew should be a lovely thick consistency now, without too much liquid remaining. Season with another pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{to taste}.

Once the pork is out of your oven cut it into thin slices.

Finally, time to plate up! Serve your pork slices on top of your crushed new potatoes and roasted red peppers, top with your butter bean stew. Dig in!